<p>If i make an object initialize it and pass to a function for change, it is reflected from where it is called. But in case of object of Integer class it is not reflected.</p>  <pre><code>//a is int Classinh inh=new Classinh();      A obj=new A();     obj.a=7;     inh.function(obj);      int i=1;     inh.function(i);     Integer j=new Integer(10);     System.out.println(obj.a+" "+i+" "+j); } private void function(A ob){     ob.a++; } private void function(int a){     a++; } private void function(Integer a){     a++; } </code></pre>